# LAB 01 – Enterprise Device Hardening & Initial Configuration

## Overview

This lab prepares a Cisco switch for production deployment by applying enterprise security best practices. The configuration includes device hardening, secure local and remote access, management VLAN configuration, password protection, SSH, and verification procedures.

## Skills Learned

- Enterprise device hardening
- Secure console configuration
- SSH configuration
- Local user authentication
- Password encryption
- Management VLAN configuration
- Switch management
- Configuration verification
- Basic troubleshooting

## Technologies

- Cisco IOS
- SSH Version 2
- RSA Encryption
- VLAN 99
- Local Authentication

## Verification

- show ip ssh
- show ip interface brief
- show running-config
- show vlan brief
- show crypto key mypubkey rsa

## Lessons Learned

This lab demonstrates that securing a network device begins before it is connected to the production network. Proper device hardening reduces security risks and establishes a secure foundation for future network services.

